#Text=Major snowstorm sweeps across Eastern US
#Text=Sunday , February 7 , 2010

#Text=A major winter storm , which has been nicknamed by some as " Snowmageddon " , has pummeled parts of the U.S. Middle Atlantic region , dumping up to 19 inches ( 50 centimeters ) of snow in some parts of the Washington area .
#Text=The National Weather Service is predicting as much as 24 to 30 inches ( 60 to 75 cm ) of snow for the Washington , D.C. region by late Saturday .
#Text=The storm brought high winds and low visibility , with winds gusting at 56 miles per hour ( 93 kilometers per hour ) along the coast .
#Text=Life in the nation 's capital ground to a halt with the federal government and most businesses closing early on Friday and residents warned to stay off the snow-clogged roads .
#Text=Hundreds of thousands of homes were without power as the wet snow weighed heavily on trees and power lines .
#Text=Power lines in some areas have been brought down by the heavy snow .
#Text=The Weather Service issued blizzard and winter storm warnings for states reaching from Virginia and West Virginia up to Maryland , Pennsylvania , Delaware , and New Jersey .
#Text=Forecasters say this could be the largest recorded snowfall in Washington , rivaling a storm , known as the Knickerbocker Storm , that hit the city nearly 90 years ago , in January 1922 .
#Text=The largest amount of snowfall recorded so far has been in Elkridge , Maryland , reporting 32 inches ( 81 cm ) .
#Text=The 1922 storm was named the Knickerbocker Storm for a theater where 98 people were killed when the building 's roof collapsed due to heavy snow .
#Text=Snowfall in that storm measured 28 inches ( 71 cm ) .
#Text=Airlines and airports across the region have canceled flights and train service has been disrupted .

#Text=Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport suspended flight operations for the day while nearby Washington Dulles International Airport reported only a few international flights would be departing .
#Text=Baltimore/Washington International Thurgood Marshall Airport reported most flights were canceled .
#Text=Flights at Philadelphia International Airport are also canceled .
#Text=Amtrak announced that it was canceling a number of trains between Washington and New York City , along with service from Washington to cities in the south .
#Text=The Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority , known as the Metro locally , has suspended bus service and above ground train service .
#Text=Underground subway service is running at 30 minute intervals .
#Text=As the storm approached , residents emptied supermarket shelves , stocking up on food and other supplies , especially due to Super Bowl XLIV which will be held on Sunday .
#Text=Local area sports teams in Washington , D.C. will still play games as scheduled .
#Text=People are urged to take the Metro to see the games and not use the roads .
#Text=Impromptu snowball fights have also broken with some people going as far as to organize them over Facebook and Twitter .
#Text=The winter weather has already been blamed for hundreds of road accidents .

#Text=So far two fatalities have been reported , a father and son who were rendering aid to a stranded motorist on Interstate 81 in Virginia , when an approaching tractor-trailer jackknifed and killed the pair .
#Text=This is the second major snowstorm to hit the region in less than two months .
